<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
This species was first recorded from Israel by 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.3391/bir.2018.7.3.05" author="Steger, J" journalOrPublisher="BioInvasions Records" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="245 - 257" refId="B213" refString="Steger, J, Stockinger, M, Ivkic, A, Galil, B, Albano, PG, 2018. New records of non-indigenous molluscs from the eastern Mediterranean Sea. BioInvasions Records 7: 245 - 257, DOI: https://doi.org/10.3391/bir.2018.7.3.05" title="New records of non-indigenous molluscs from the eastern Mediterranean Sea." url="https://doi.org/10.3391/bir.2018.7.3.05" volume="7" year="2018">Steger et al. (2018)</bibRefCitation>
based on three living individuals from Palmachim, southern Israel. We here report multiple living individuals all along the Israeli coast, confirming its establishment. The species shows a broad distribution in the Eastern Mediterranean ranging from Greece to Turkey and Cyprus (
<bibRefCitation author="Micali, P" journalOrPublisher="Bollettino Malacologico" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="40 - 49" refId="B151" refString="Micali, P, Siragusa, F, Agamennone, F, Germana, A, Sbrana, C, 2017. Karpathos Island (Greece) and its Indo-Pacific alien species, Part 1. Bollettino Malacologico 53: 40 - 49" title="Karpathos Island (Greece) and its Indo-Pacific alien species, Part 1." volume="53" year="2017">Micali et al. 2017</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Stamouli, C" journalOrPublisher="Mediterranean Marine Science" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="534 - 556" refId="B212" refString="Stamouli, C, Akel, EHK, Azzurro, E, Bakiu, R, Bas, AA, Bitar, G, Boyaci, Y, Cakalli, M, Corsini-Foka, M, Crocetta, F, Dragicevic, B, Dulcic, J, Durucan, F, El, Z, Erguden, D, Filiz, H, Giardina, F, Giovos, I, Goenuelal, O, Hemida, F, Kassar, A, Kondylatos, G, Macali, A, Mancini, E, Ovalis, P, De M, Pavicic M, Rabaoui, L, Rizkalla, SI, Tiralongo, F, Turan, C, Vrdoljak, D, Yapici, S, Zenetos, A, 2017. New Mediterranean biodiversity records (December 2017). Mediterranean Marine Science 18: 534 - 556" title="New Mediterranean biodiversity records (December 2017)." volume="18" year="2017">Stamouli et al. 2017</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Angelidis, A" journalOrPublisher="Xenophora Taxonomy" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="3 - 10" refId="B23" refString="Angelidis, A, Polyzoulis, G, 2018. New distributional records of four Indo-Pacific species from Astypalaia Island, South Aegean Sea, Greece. Xenophora Taxonomy 21: 3 - 10" title="New distributional records of four Indo-Pacific species from Astypalaia Island, South Aegean Sea, Greece." volume="21" year="2018">Angelidis and Polyzoulis 2018</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.12681/mms.18099" author="Chartosia, N" journalOrPublisher="Mediterranean Marine Science" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="398 - 415" refId="B68" refString="Chartosia, N, Anastasiadis, D, Bazairi, H, Crocetta, F, Deidun, A, Despalatovic, M, Martino, VD, Dimitriou, N, Dragicevic, B, Dulcic, J, Durucan, F, Hasbek, D, Ketsilis-Rinis, V, Kleitou, P, Lipej, L, Macali, A, Marchini, A, Ousselam, M, Piraino, S, Stancanelli, B, Theodosiou, M, Tiralongo, F, Todorova, V, Trkov, D, Yapici, S, 2018. New Mediterranean Biodiversity Records (July 2018). Mediterranean Marine Science 19: 398 - 415, DOI: https://doi.org/10.12681/mms.18099" title="New Mediterranean Biodiversity Records (July 2018)." url="https://doi.org/10.12681/mms.18099" volume="19" year="2018">Chartosia et al. 2018</bibRefCitation>
). Its final taxonomic assignment requires the clarification of the relation between several other 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Jousseaume" authorityYear="1884" class="Gastropoda" family="Triphoridae" genus="Viriola" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Viriola" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Viriola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
such as 
<taxonomicName genus="V." lsidName="V. corrugata" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="corrugata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">V. corrugata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Hinds, 1843), 
<taxonomicName genus="V." lsidName="V. senafirensis" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="senafirensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">V. senafirensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Sturany, 1903), and 
<taxonomicName genus="V." lsidName="V. tricincta" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="tricincta">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">V. tricincta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Dunker, 1882) (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.3897/zse.92.5936" author="Albano, PG" journalOrPublisher="Zoosystematics and Evolution" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="33 - 78" refId="B13" refString="Albano, PG, Bakker, PAJ, 2016. Annotated catalogue of the types of Triphoridae (Mollusca, Gastropoda) in the Museum fuer Naturkunde, Berlin, with lectotype designations. Zoosystematics and Evolution 92: 33 - 78, DOI: https://doi.org/10.3897/zse.92.5936" title="Annotated catalogue of the types of Triphoridae (Mollusca, Gastropoda) in the Museum fuer Naturkunde, Berlin, with lectotype designations." url="https://doi.org/10.3897/zse.92.5936" volume="92" year="2016">Albano and Bakker 2016</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.3897/zse.93.10039" author="Albano, PG" journalOrPublisher="Zoosystematics and Evolution" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="45 - 94" refId="B18" refString="Albano, PG, Bakker, PAJ, Janssen, R, Eschner, A, 2017. An illustrated catalogue of Rudolf Sturany's type specimens in the Naturhistorisches Museum Wien, Austria (NHMW): Red Sea gastropods. Zoosystematics and Evolution 93: 45 - 94, DOI: https://doi.org/10.3897/zse.93.10039" title="An illustrated catalogue of Rudolf Sturany's type specimens in the Naturhistorisches Museum Wien, Austria (NHMW): Red Sea gastropods." url="https://doi.org/10.3897/zse.93.10039" volume="93" year="2017">Albano et al. 2017</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.3897/zse.95.32803" author="Albano, PG" journalOrPublisher="Zoosystematics and Evolution" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="161 - 308" refId="B16" refString="Albano, PG, Bakker, PAJ, Sabelli, B, 2019. Annotated catalogue of the types of Triphoridae (Mollusca, Gastropoda) in the Natural History Museum of the United Kingdom, London. Zoosystematics and Evolution 95: 161 - 308, DOI: https://doi.org/10.3897/zse.95.32803" title="Annotated catalogue of the types of Triphoridae (Mollusca, Gastropoda) in the Natural History Museum of the United Kingdom, London." url="https://doi.org/10.3897/zse.95.32803" volume="95" year="2019">2019</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
